nt's career.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEcologistszAustraliavBiography. 0aForest canopy ecology. 0aRain forest ecology. 0aWomen ecologistszAustraliavBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Science & Technology.2bisacsh1 aBurgess, Edward, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBurgess, James, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPrance, Ghillean T., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPrance, Ghillean T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300153415?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300153415423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300153415/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles